{"build_type":"library","description":"Layer-2 eventfd-replacement, AWAIT side (wake-object-eventfd-replacement-DESIGN section 3). Blocks the calling thread until the doorbell at address `word` is announced ready (its marker differs from `expected`). This is the [= eventfd read] role. Delegates to the layer-1 suspend primitive, which provides the userspace fast path (returns with NO syscall if the marker already differs from `expected`) and the FUTEX_WAIT block + re-check loop otherwise. Returns the observed marker value. Replaces the inline FUTEX_WAIT (sys 202) park in the scheduler worker park path. No counter/consume in v1: the doorbell is a binary readiness flag (the design's counter+waiters-flag are a later extension).","module_name":"suspend-caller-awaiting-doorbell-readiness","package_name":"suspend-caller-awaiting-doorbell-readiness","function_definitions":{"suspend-caller-awaiting-doorbell-readiness":{"return_type":"i64","parameter_definitions":[{"parameter_name":"word","parameter_type":"i64"},{"parameter_name":"expected","parameter_type":"i64"}],"execution_instructions":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"zero","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":0},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"one","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":1},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"two","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":2},{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"sixteen","variable_type":"i64","assignment_operation":"literal","source_target":16},{"instruction_type":"array_read","dest":"c","base":"word","index":"zero","scale":8},{"instruction_type":"conditional_branch","condition_type":"numeric_compare","operator":"!=","lhs":{"value":"c"},"rhs":{"value":"zero"},"branch_on_success":[{"instruction_type":"variable_declaration","variable_name":"cdec","variable_type":"i64","assignment_